Gluster 3.2: Installing the Gluster Storage Software Appliance[
Installing the Gluster Storage Software Appliance>>]

Before installing Gluster Storage Software Appliance, verify that your
environment matches the minimum requirements described in this section.

*General*

Verify the following:

* Centralized time servers are available (required in clustered
environments)

*Note:* The boot device must be =<2.2 TB.

*Storage Servers*

* Intel/AMD x86 64-bit processor
* Disk: 10 GB minimum
* Memory: 2 GB minimum

*Hardware*

Verify the following:

* All hardware is on the Red Hat HCL (Hardware Compatibility List) of
version 5 and is available at https://hardware.redhat.com/

*Note:* Any other hardware not listed in Red Hat HCL may also work, but
has not been tested widely.

*Networking Requirements*

Verify the following:

* Gigabit Ethernet
* 10 Gigabit Ethernet

